Defendant Troy Allen Muns in court with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Defendant Troy Allen Muns in custody.  
Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court for Sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 72 MONTHS EACH COUNT, CONCURRENT with EACH OTHER with credit for 166 days.  The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 36 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 36 MONTHS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment- aoda program completed at House of Corrections may satisfy if deemed appropriate by department of corrections- complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Obtain Mental health evaluation and complete follow-up care/treatment;
* No contact with victims Airene T., Leona  M., and the Dunkin Donuts located at 622 West Wisconsin Ave.;
*Obtain/maintain employment- work at least 30 hours per week;
*Participate in education/vocational training while incarcerated and during extended supervision;
*Pay dna surcharge on one count only;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of supervision period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

The state in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $1128.67 payable to State of Wisconsin Crime Victim Compensation Program-to be paid first.  The Court ordered all financial obligations and restitution to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms.  Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated. 
